                            <comment id="15129787" author="sachin aggarwal" created="Wed, 3 Feb 2016 04:58:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As of Spark 2.0 (not yet released), Spark does not use Akka any more. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-5293&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-5293&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;can you check with latest 2.0 build, to see if similar problem exists.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15141992" author="lin@exabeam.com" created="Thu, 11 Feb 2016 00:09:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I haven&apos;t tested with the master code but looking at the source it almost certain has the same issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15141998" author="lin@exabeam.com" created="Thu, 11 Feb 2016 00:13:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There also seems to be no way to specify bounded blocking mailbox for ActorReceiverSupervisor, which would solve this. Only way I can think of is adding a storeSync to ActorReceiver.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
